!------------------------- D2 Setup(Windows) -------------------------! 
-   Download appropriate windows binary from https://github.com/terrastruct/d2/releases ex: d2-v0.7.1-windows-amd64.msi
-   Run the the binary
-   Add D2 to your path:
        ~ Window Start search environment variables
        ~ New variable
        ~ Name your variable and add the file path to the d2 executable ex: C:\Program Files\d2
        ~ Restart terminal
-   Test D2 was installed successfully:
        ~ In a terminal(Command prompt or powershell)
        ~ d2 --version
        ~ echo 'x -> y -> z' > in.d2
        ~ d2 -w input.d2 out.svg
-   Take the tour at https://d2lang.com/ to get familiar with the tool
    
!------------------------- D2 commands -------------------------!
+ Basic command to output svg
-   d2 --theme=6 --dark-theme=7 -l elk --pad 10 ./helloworld.d2
        {
            --theme: set a light theme
            --dark-theme: set a dark theme
            -l: set a layout {
                dagre(default): Fast, general-purpose hierarchical layout that works well out of the box, but can produce suboptimal edge crossings on large or dense graphs.
                elk: High-quality, enterprise-grade hierarchical layout with excellent spacing and crossing minimization, but slower and heavier than other options.
                tala(requires download):Deterministic grid-based layout that gives precise structural control, but provides no automatic graph optimization or intelligence.
            }
            --pad: set your padding
        }

